properties.Name: InsuranceProductRelationshipType
properties.Description:
The nature of the relationship between two or more products for the associated period.

Ex:
- Compatible Product
- Comparable Product
- Replacement Product
- Bundled Product
- Included Product
- Optional Product
- Family / Line Relationship
- Marketing Relationship
- Underwriting Relationship

Insurance Product 1:  Homeowner's Insurance
Insurance Product 2:  Personal Liability Umbrella Policy
Insurance Product Relationship Type:  Provides extended coverage

Insurance Product 1:  Homeowner's Insurance
Insurance Product 2:  Vehicle Insurance
Insurance Product Relationship Type:  Available as bundle

Insurance Product 1:  Boat Insurance
Insurance Product 2:  Vehicle Insurance
Insurance Product Relationship Type:  Multi-policy Discount

Insurance Product 1:  Renters Policy
Insurance Product 2:  Flood Policy
Insurance Product Relationship Type:  Flood is required to cover flood damage

Insurance Product 1:  Earthquake Insurance
Insurance Product 2:  Homeowners Insurance
Insurance Product Relationship Type:  Required in CA.

In California to obtain CEA coverage, you must first have a companion residential insurance policy written through a CEA participating insurance company.
